Create a reusable UI invoice named mtk-invoice using:

HTML
SCSS
Vanilla JavaScript
Bootstrap 5
Modern Material Design styles
Material Design icon-style UI
No external libraries

Always create a JS class for mtk-invoice and initialize it inside the JS file itself.

Rules:

The component is wrapped in a display:block element:
<mtk-invoice class="mtk-invoice">
The root element uses .mtk-invoice
All styles must be scoped to .mtk-invoice
No global styles or IDs
Publish click events using wc.publish
Subscribe to all 4-mtk-invoice events using wc.subscribe
Create an onMessage function to pass to wc.subscribe
Data must be JSON driven
Any/all data must come from mtk-invoice.config.js
Must wait for the element to be available in the DOM because the component may be dynamically loaded using:
<wc-include href="..."></wc-include>
All wc.publish calls must first log the message using wc.log
Use semantic HTML
Keyboard accessible
Visible focus states
ADA compliant
Mobile responsive
Material floating labels for forms
Use SCSS only
No CSS files
No frameworks
No React
No Vue
No Angular
No iframes
Use <wc-include href="..."/> whenever external content is needed

Files required:

mtk-invoice.config.js
mtk-invoice.scss
mtk-invoice.html
mtk-invoice.js

Invoice Requirements:

Modern Material Design invoice layout
Sticky action toolbar on top
Company logo area
Invoice header section
Customer information section
Invoice metadata section:
Invoice number
Invoice date
Due date
Status
Dynamic invoice items table
Add/remove line items
Qty, description, price, subtotal
Auto-calculate:
subtotal
tax
discount
grand total
Notes section
Terms section
Payment methods section
Print invoice button
Download PDF button placeholder
Send invoice button
Save draft button
Responsive mobile invoice layout
Material buttons with ripple-style interaction
Optional left navigation drawer on desktop
Collapse navigation into hamburger menu on mobile
Smooth Material transitions and animations
Empty states
Validation states
Inline editable invoice fields
Currency formatting
JSON-configurable tax rates and company info
Example dummy data in config

Behavior:

Emit events such as:
mtk-invoice:save
mtk-invoice:send
mtk-invoice:print
mtk-invoice:item-added
mtk-invoice:item-removed
Listen for:
4-mtk-invoice-refresh
4-mtk-invoice-update
4-mtk-invoice-load

Design:

Clean modern Material Design
Soft shadows
Floating labels
Accessible colors
Subtle hover effects
Mobile-first responsive layout
Minimal rounded corners
Professional SaaS invoice appearance

Output Requirements:

Always provide FULL FILES only
Never provide partial snippets
Never show patches/diffs
Always provide downloadable ZIP named:
x.zip
Never modify anything outside the explicit request
Use:
NYCMEL/nala-website GitHub Repository

as the base repository for all future changes.
